description: Gets a list of migrations between Amazon Lex V1 and Amazon Lex V2.

nested_items.name: migrationSummaries
nested_items.description: An array of summaries for migrations from Amazon Lex V1 to Amazon Lex V2. To see details of the migration, use the migrationId from the summary in a call to the operation.

nested_items.name: migrationId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier that Amazon Lex assigned to the migration.

nested_items.name: v1BotName
nested_items.description: The name of the Amazon Lex V1 bot that is the source of the migration.

nested_items.name: v1BotVersion
nested_items.description: The version of the Amazon Lex V1 bot that is the source of the migration.

nested_items.name: v1BotLocale
nested_items.description: The locale of the Amazon Lex V1 bot that is the source of the migration.

nested_items.name: v2BotId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the Amazon Lex V2 that is the destination of the migration.

nested_items.name: v2BotRole
nested_items.description: The IAM role that Amazon Lex uses to run the Amazon Lex V2 bot.

nested_items.name: migrationStatus
nested_items.description: The status of the operation. When the status is COMPLETE the bot is available in Amazon Lex V2. There may be alerts and warnings that need to be resolved to complete the migration.

nested_items.name: migrationStrategy
nested_items.description: The strategy used to conduct the migration.

nested_items.name: migrationTimestamp
nested_items.description: The date and time that the migration started.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: If the response is truncated, it includes a pagination token that you can specify in your next request to fetch the next page of migrations.
